  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Deborah Weston is seriously considering going to New York, and needs a suitable gown to wear there. She gives a detailed account of the local &quot;notice battle,&quot; that is to say the struggle to get the local clergy to read notices of anti-slavery meetings. Deborah comments: &quot;The temperance people are trying to get up as efficient an organization as ours.&quot; She retells an amusing anecdote told by Dr. Jewitt, &quot;the temperance man,&quot; in a lecture.</subfield>
